        "text": "We have at least two choices for problem solving. We can just start pushing things around to see what will happen. Sometimes that is the only way to proceed. That is exactly how babies learn, that and copying. However, sometimes, often we can push metaphors and models around first (if we have them handy)‚Äîavoiding the consequence of trying to move real things and people and institutions, just to see what can happen. We experiment in live systems or in models of live systems. \n"
